With all of this distance learning decision making going on, who could use a glass of wine? I know we could use a few!

Join the Virtual Mammoth Wine Walk and support the Mammoth Mountain Community Foundation.
All wine for the ghost package has been donated, allowing MMCF to receive *100%* of all ghost package purchases, and 50% of proceeds on all other packages.

This year, MMCF is supporting MUSD through a technology donation and will be offering after school tutoring for all students K-12 to help ensure all of our students are able to keep up during distance learning. Please help us show them how much we appreciate their support!

For more details: https://mammothfoundation.org/pages/mammoth-wine-walk

Estamos buscando aportes y comentarios de todas las familias de MES para ayudarnos a planificar el futuro del PTO. Queremos saber de todos para poder servir mejor a nuestros hijos y a la escuela, así que ¡tómese 5 minutos para completar nuestra breve encuesta!

No podemos hacer nada de esto sin ti, ¡y no nos gustaría que fuera de otra manera!

shared_text:
Yosemite National Park
May 7 at 4:00 PM ·

We have big news: we're launching a Yosemite virtual junior ranger program, so that kids can earn a special badge from home while the park is closed.

To learn how to earn your badge, visit https://www.nps.gov/yose/planyourvisit/virtual-yosemite.htm

Follow the instructions to download the worksheet (in English or Spanish) and send your completed pages to us. While you're waiting for your badge to arrive in the mail, find a badge coloring sheet, along with more art and coloring activities, at the link above!

1: #WeLoveMESstaff - share your favorite MES memories and pictures using this hashtag (and don't forget to tag us so that your posts will show up here for the staff to read Mammoth Elementary School PTO

post_text:
Did you know....
Your kids can legally vote?!?!
While you are practicing your civic duty to vote today, bring your kids along! Talk about WHAT you are voting for, WHY you are voting, and better yet... they can fill in your ballot, and put it through the feeder. It is SO important that you get out there to vote today, and just as important that we teach our kids to do the same.
I'll see you at the polls! (after school pick-up)
- And don't forget to make sure they walk out with a sticker

post_text:
Thank you to all who attended, Volunteered, donated to our Gala! It was a HUGE Success! Numbers are still coming in, but it looks like we hit or were VERY CLOSE to our goal of raising $25,000!!
Now lets Celebrate! Our Final PTO Meeting of the school year will be on May 31st! (NOTE THE DATE CHANGE!) at Gomezs! It will be a SHORT meeting with a meet and greet following!
